t, rendering it nonfunctional in the event of failing to load the script, making the most crucial part of the portfolio website inaccessible to visitors. In pursuit of a solution, I opted for a different approach.</p><p>I found that setting the carousel wrapper to <code>overflow-hidden</code> and embracing relatively new CSS scroll properties like <code>scroll-snap</code> presented a comparable yet JavaScript-independent solution, where tabbing actually worked, as the browser natively scrolls to tabbed items.</p><p>All I had to do now is to enhance the native foundation by adding custom drag events, updating the <code>scrollLeft</code> value of the carousel.</p><p>Finally, everything looked and worked as expected:</p><astro-island uid="1JEVYu" prefix="r19" component-url="/_astro/image.8cf812a2.js" component-export="default" renderer-url="/_astro/client.c2e853c0.js" props="{&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quot;image&quot;],&quot;alt&quot;:[0,&quot;Carousel using native css scroll properties when tabbing through&quot;],&quot;_key&quot;:[0,&quot;ebf50d8c12eb&quot;],&quot;asset&quot;:[0,{&quot;metadata&quot;:[0,{&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quot;sanity.imageMetadata&quot;],&quot;palette&quot;:[0,{&quot;lightVibrant&quot;:[0,{&quot;title&quot;:[0,&quot;#000&quot;],&quot;population&quot;:[0,0.25],&quot;background&quot;:[0,&quot;#f7e598&quot;],&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quot;sanity.imagePaletteSwatch&quot;],&quot;foreground&quot;:[0,&quot;#000&quot;]}],&quot;darkVibrant&quot;:[0,{&quot;title&quot;:[0,&quot;#fff&quot;],&quot;population&quot;:[0,0.16],&quot;background&quot;:[0,&quot;#113374&quot;],&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quot;sanity.imagePaletteSwatch&quot;],&quot;foreground&quot;:[0,&quot;#fff&quot;]}],&quot;lightMuted&quot;:[0,{&quot;title&quot;:[0,&quot;#fff&quot;],&quot;population&quot;:[0,0.25],&quot;background&quot;:[0,&quot;#b1a17d&quot;],&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quot;sanity.imagePaletteSwatch&quot;],&quot;foreground&quot;:[0,&quot;#000&quot;]}],&quot;vibrant&quot;:[0,{&quot;_type&quot;:[0,&quo